    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, our offensive engine is firing on all cylinders, led by the high-upside pairing of **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (75.89). **Mickey Moniak** benefits from a massive 14% park factor boost and a highly favorable matchup against Glasnow; his ability to exploit the pitcher\u2019s slow delivery makes him our premier SB threat. **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, meanwhile, is surging due to a +15% efficiency gain against the matchup with Wacha. We are also leaning heavily into **Tyler Soderstrom** (72.72) in the OF1 slot; his combination of a 10% park advantage and a significant SP skill edge against Martin makes him a high-floor, high-ceiling play that warrants his spot in the heart of our order.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was leaving **Alex Freeland** (58.63) out of the active lineup. Despite a robust park factor and favorable SP matchup, his assignment to the #9 hole dragged his efficiency below the threshold established by **Max Muncy** (63.98), who benefits from a cleaner path to RBI production. We are closely monitoring the risks associated with **Corbin Carroll** (62.60) and **Austin Riley** (71.42); **Corbin Carroll** faces a formidable 3.09 xERA starter in Fisher, placing a heavy reliance on his SB-friendly conditions to maintain his value, while **Austin Riley** remains a lock despite a minor penalty for facing an elite defensive catcher. Elsewhere, **Vinnie Pasquantino** (65.80) continues to be a mandatory start, bolstered by a 14% dynamic platoon edge that effectively mitigates the challenge of facing Schlittler. Ensure all lineup configurations are locked to account for the volatile SP environments facing **Luis Campusano** and **Trevor Story**, as their efficiency scores remain the most sensitive to late-breaking lineup shifts.",
